    "body": "Hi @SvenMeyer it looks like you're requiring a module that isn't properly installed. The way we name the package now is `@truffle/hdwallet-provider`. You may need to change both the import and the reference in your `package.json`. It seems you have two truffle configuration files, so it is worth checking that they are both referring to the same package. But really you should prefer the `truffle-config` file, and it may be worth deleting the other file so there isn't any confusion. \r\n\r\nThe important part is you should be installing the most current package and you should be consistent on the naming throughout your project. Can you try to make the change and see if it resolves your issue?",
